@startuml UML_StateMachine

' Concept #24 — UML State Machine Diagram
' Shows: states and transitions for an entity over its lifetime

title State Machine — User Authentication Flow

[*] --> Unauthenticated : Initial state

Unauthenticated --> Authenticating : User submits credentials
Authenticating --> Invalid : Wrong email/password (after 3 attempts → Locked)
Authenticating --> MFARequired : Valid credentials + MFA enabled
Authenticating --> Authenticated : Valid credentials + MFA disabled
Invalid --> Unauthenticated : User can retry
Authenticating --> Locked : 5 consecutive failures

Locked --> Unauthenticated : Email unlock link clicked (30 min expiry)

MFARequired --> Authenticated : Valid TOTP code (±1 step window)
MFARequired --> MFAFailed : Invalid TOTP code (3 attempts)
MFAFailed --> Locked : Max TOTP failures reached
MFARequired --> Unauthenticated : Cancel / timeout (5 min)

Authenticated --> TokenRefresh : Access token expires (15 min)
TokenRefresh --> Authenticated : Valid refresh token (7 day)
TokenRefresh --> Unauthenticated : Expired/invalid refresh token → re-login

Authenticated --> Unauthenticated : User logout (revoke refresh token)
Authenticated --> Unauthenticated : Admin force-logout
Authenticated --> [*] : Account deleted

state Authenticated {
    [*] --> Active
    Active --> Idle : No activity 30 min
    Idle --> Active : User action
    Idle --> SessionExpired : Idle > 60 min
    SessionExpired --> [*]
}

@enduml

