@startuml UML_Activity

' Concept #24 — UML Activity Diagram (like a flowchart, but richer)
' Shows: workflow with branching, forking, joining

title Activity Diagram — Concept Learning Workflow

|Developer|
start

:Select concept category;
:Browse available concepts;
:Choose concept to study;

fork
    |Developer|
    :Read theory + explanation;
    :Study code examples;
    :Check time/space complexity;

fork again
    |Developer|
    :Watch algorithm visualization;

end fork

:Attempt challenge;

|Backend|
:Receive submission;
:Compile user code (sandbox);
:Run test cases;
:Evaluate correctness;

if (All tests passed?) then (yes)
    |Backend|
    :Award points;
    :Update progress;
    :Update leaderboard;

    |Developer|
    :View results + solution;
    :Read optimal solution explanation;

    if (More challenges?) then (yes)
        :Select next challenge;
        backward :Attempt challenge;
    else (no)
        :Mark concept completed;
    endif
else (no)
    |Backend|
    :Return failure details;
    :Show hint;

    |Developer|
    :Review failing test cases;
    :Debug solution;
    backward :Attempt challenge;
endif

:Check learning path progress;

if (Category complete?) then (yes)
    :Unlock next category;
    :Celebrate milestone!;
endif

stop

@enduml
